15 WHEREAS, Lawrence Ervin Bearden was a passionate advocate for
16 education, serving twelve (12) years on the Smackover School District’s Board
17 of Directors, including serving as President of the Smackover School
18 District’s Board of Directors; and
19
20 WHEREAS, Lawrence Ervin Bearden later served four (4) terms on the
21 Southern Arkansas University Foundation’s Board of Governors, including three
22 (3) years as Chair of Southern Arkansas University Foundation’s Board of
23 Governors; and
24
25 WHEREAS, in 2016, former Governor Asa Hutchinson appointed Lawrence
26 Ervin Bearden to the Board of Trustees of Southern Arkansas University, where
27 he played a key role in advancing the university during a period of
28 significant growth, including the construction of new residence halls, the
29 President's House, the Poultry Education Facility, and the renovation of the
30 Alumni Center at both Southern Arkansas University and Southern Arkansas
31 University Tech; and
32
33 WHEREAS, Lawrence Ervin Bearden's generosity and commitment to
34 education led to the establishment of an endowment for the Southern Arkansas
35 University band program, resulting in the naming of the band hall in honor of
36 his father-in-law, Richard O. Oliver, Southern Arkansas University's first
